data.title: PCAOB awards record 676 student scholarships
data.meta_description: The Public Company Accounting Oversight Board announced its largest-ever cohort of students will receive $15,000 each, up from $10,000 in previous years.
data.text:
The Public Company Accounting Oversight Board announced Thursday that a record 676 scholarship recipients will receive $15,000 each for the 2024-2025 academic year.

The number of students in this year's cohort is the largest in the PCAOB Scholars Program's history, up from 369 in 2023 and 250 in 2022. The scholarship amount increased, too, up from $10,000 previously.

The scholarship money is provided by the 2002 Sarbanes-Oxley Act, which mandates that PCAOB monetary penalties be used to fund a merit scholarship program for accounting students. Recipients are nominated by their colleges and universities, which participate in the program. The goal of the program is to support students who want to pursue a career in the accounting profession and to raise awareness about opportunities in accounting.

Since 2011, the Scholars Program has awarded $32.56 million in scholarships to 2,918 recipients. This year it expanded its reach to community college transfer students as well as Historically Black Colleges and Universities — 12 HBCUs are represented among the 2024 scholars.

"Congratulations to our 2024-2025 PCAOB Scholars," PCAOB chair Erica Williams said in a statement. "Having talented and diverse people join the accounting and auditing profession is key to the future of investor protection, and we are proud that our PCAOB Scholars Program helps outstanding individuals, such as this group of students, along this career path."
